title: Christians, Inc.
content:
Christians, Inc. is a family owned and operated insurance restoration company established in 1990. Working out of our 18,000 square foot office, warehouse, and showroom in Chanhassen, MN, we have served the needs of over 13,000 businesses and homeowners throughout the Twin Cities metro area.

Visit ChristiansInc.com

WEBSITE UPDATE & REDESIGN

Christians, Inc. has been online since 1999 and hired my services to assist with creating a new look for their website as well as update content to match or outperform their industry competitors online.

Project Requirements:

  • Contact Form
  • Update Photos
  • Update Information about Services

Project Achievements:

  • Competitive analysis of industry competitors' websites
  • Created content based off of analysis to provide better services
  • Added new content other competitors lacked such as modern comparative images, easy drop-down contact forms, and FAQs about services.
  • Added COVID-19 information & business operation facts based on research from other restoration companies, WHO, and industry standards for emergency services.
  • Added new ways interested clients can contact Christians, Inc. with placed advertisements on the sidebar/footer.
  • Arranged content based on how users would easily find information, especially during an emergency.
  • Edited project before/after photos for a brighter appearance and to provide website look & feel uniformity.

MN CHAOS SOFTBALL

A secondary goal was to create a website location for MN Chaos Softball within the ChristiansInc.com website, as the owners of the company have been coaching and sponsoring the local team for over 10 years.

The softball team website required content included having a photo gallery and contact information.

With this new website, returning or interested players, parents, news stations, and local community events can contact Christians, Inc. to learn about MN Chaos Softball, sponsorship opportunities, and community involvement actions.

The website layout within ChristiansInc.com also takes on a different look & feel to help users identify that they are within a new section of the website specifically dedicated to MN Chaos softball.

New and returning players can also pre-register for the season as well as keep up-to-date with events posted on the MN Chaos homepage. These events also sync to their phone calendars and the new website makes it easy to users to stay connected at all times.

title: Bobcat Doosan
content:
Bobcat is a global brand with employees and manufacturing facilities worldwide. We are proud of what we create, the value we provide and the relationships we build – all while helping people succeed. Customers use our machines and technologies to accomplish more in construction, agriculture, landscaping, rental, grounds maintenance, utilities and other applications.  Both the people behind our brand and the equipment we manufacture are tough, agile and versatile. Bobcat equipment fosters a sense of pride and inspires confidence on even the most challenging job sites.

WWW.BOBCAT.COM

Sales & Marketing Co-op

PROJECTS

  • Edited, added and arranged internal website for Bobcat DealerNET and Doosan DealerNET content using a content management site (CMS) called Salesforce and Teamsite.  HTML and CSS were also used while editing.  These languages have been utilized on the job at Doosan Bobcat Company while arranging the internal website and crafting the bi-weekly Dealer Update e-newsletter. 
  • Analyzed data monthly using Oracle and intranet systems, spoke with product influencers and compiled data into Excel reports to be distributed.
  • Organized, assembled and edited weekly email content using Salesforce Exact Target for Bobcat and Doosan.
  • Researched, analyzed and created presentation material for benchmark research projects on competitor companies and industry trends.
  • Provided moving logistic assistance and file merging during the Bobcat Doosan headquarters remodel. I lead the intern team with tasked projects including converting physical files into digital files, relocating equipment to new office locations, and creating internal communication items with the marketing staff detailing building remodel updates.
